      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s already semi-documented in the ClipPath_nonfinite test: https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/master:third_party/skia/tests/PathTest.cpp;drc\u003d282f8f468542cd7b282eb8c82b2dcd952dd14e48;l\u003d5176\n\nBeforehand, the conservative clip was was allowing this test to pass. Afterwards, SkBitmapDevice\u0027s SkRasterClip\u0027s handling came into play and that\u0027s where we hit this inconsistency with SkRegion::setPath.\n\nI don\u0027t disagree with any of your initial feelings, and perhaps the right approach is to leave SkRegion::setPath as-is and adjust the unit test expectations and have SkCanvas::onClipPath universally handle non-finite paths.",
